				\begin{document}$$\,{humangene} \sim {microb}{e}_{1}+...+{microb}{e}_{n}$$\end{document}humangene~microbe1+...+microben

As a second form of association identification with the added benefit of statistical inference to control for false positives, we used a mixed effect linear regression approach for each microbe/DEG pair that had a non-zero coefficient coming out of the Lasso regressions. We transformed the gene/microbe abundances with the same approaches as above and fit models of the form:2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
